<item>
            <title>[FLINK-7968] Deduplicate serializer classes between runtime and queryable state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7968</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some serializer classes where duplicated into &lt;tt&gt;flink-queryable-state&lt;/tt&gt; to avoid a dependency on &lt;tt&gt;flink-runtime&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proper solution here is to move the classes to the shared &lt;tt&gt;flink-core&lt;/tt&gt; project, because these classes are actually useful in a series of API utilities and they do not have any dependency on other flink classes at all.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
